    "body": "Happens when head_slot doesn't change over intervals. \r\nThe `speedo` accumulates `(head_slot, instant)` with same `head_slot` for different instants.\r\nSo the distance calculation here returns 0.0 we get a `Vec<f64>` of zeros.\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/e4c56e6c5c929a3112c4a08852be54345b0acc0a/beacon_node/client/src/notifier.rs#L269-L279\r\n\r\nHence, the function returns `Some(0.0)` and `est_time` returns `inf`.\r\nWe can fix this by returning `None` if `sum == 0`. \r\n\r\n```rust\r\nif count > 0 && sum > 0.0 {\r\n    Some(sum / f64::from(count as u32))\r\n} else {\r\n    None\r\n}\r\n```",
